quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  7,138,"And We made the Children of Israel pass over the sea, then they came upon a people who were devoted to some human-shaped idols of theirs. They said, “O Moses, make for us a god as they have gods.” He said, “You are truly speaking ignorantly.”"
  7,139,"“What these people are concerned with is surely doomed to perdition, and whatever they used to do is false.”"
  7,140,"He said, “Shall I seek for you a god other than Allah when He has favored you over all communities?”"
  7,141,"And recall how <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ibn Amer read it as: “And recall when He saved you…”</span>,footnotes:2:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Nafie’ read it as: “…evil punishment, killing your sons…”</span>
  7,142,"And We <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Abu Amr, Ja’far and Ya’qub read it as: “And We promised Moses thirty nights,”</span>,footnotes:2:A grammatical shift from 1<sup>st</sup> person to 3 person to 3<sup>rd</sup> person. person.
  7,143,"And when Moses came for Our appointment and his Lord<a class=""sup""><sup>d </sup></a>spoke to him, he said, “My Lord, let me see—to look upon You.” He said, “You will not see Me, but look at the mountain—if it<i class=""s"">(still) </i>resides in its place, you will see Me.” But when his Lord manifested Himself to the mountain, He turned it into <span class=",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 1<sup>st</sup> person to 3 person to 3<sup>rd</sup> person. person.,footnotes:2:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “…He turned it into flattened land,”</span>
